06/06/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The police have charged a local OSCE official with child pornography, police spokesperson Ivo Kotevski announced on Friday (June 4th). 
During a raid of the official's apartment in Skopje, the police seized several computers with videos and 30,000 pictures showing "explicit acts of child pornography". 
According to Kotevski, the suspect is a 38-year-old Norwegian national who is currently on a vacation abroad. 
(AP, MIA, Makfax, Tanjug - 04/06/10)
